title: The Fyodor Dostoevsky BBC Radio Drama Collection
subtitle: Including Crime and Punishment, The Idiot, Devils & The Brothers Karamazov
description: One of the most important and influential Russian writers of the 19th century, Fyodor Dostoevsky is admired worldwide for his great realist novels, exploring questions of morality, philosophy and the nature of existence. This compilation contains the BBC radio productions of his four most famous novels - as well as three lesser-known works and two bonus documentaries - collected together for the first time.
